{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01U3jYiebVdV8Cu511ycCi56","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the failure patterns from the digest and write feedback.md.\n\nLooking at the failures:\n\n**Pattern 1: OCR corruption - digit-for-letter substitution**\n- Braised Cod with White Wine: \"Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne\" → extracted empty\n- Drożdże Sernik: \"Drożdże Sern1k\" → extracted wrong line\n- Piernik z Śliwkami: \"P1ern1k z Śliwkami\" → extracted wrong line\n- Roasted Beet and Walnut Dip: \"Roasted Beet and Walnut D1p\" → extracted empty\n\n\n- Żurek Krakowski: \"Żurek Krakowski\" (with corruption note) → extracted garbage\n\nThe title appears on the first line but with OCR corruption where digits replace letters, causing the extractor to either return nothing or grab the wrong content entirely.\n\n**Pattern 2: Category header before title**\n- Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce: \"FISH & SEAFOOD\" on line one, actual title on line two → extractor picked the instruction body instead\n- Roasted Asparagus with Parmesan: \"VEGETABLES\" on line one, title on line two → extractor grabbed the subtitle or description\n- Órkowa Zupa: Metadata like \"Lato | Zupy | DLA 4 OSÓB | ...\" on line one, title on line two → extractor returned empty\n\n**Pattern 3: Multi-line title split by OCR**\n- Lemon Herb Roasted Vegetables: Title broken across lines with OCR errors (\"LEMON HERB RO45TED / VEGETABLES\") → extractor only captured the first fragment\n\n**Pattern 4: Title obscured by content from previous recipe**\n- Mushroom Risotto and Peach Cobbler: Files start with leftover instruction text or corrupted content from the previous page, causing the extractor to grab the wrong title from the middle of the file instead of finding the actual recipe title.\n\nNow I'm seeing three main failure patterns emerge. The OCR corruption cases affect five recipes where digits replace letters in the title itself, causing the extractor to either skip it entirely or pick something else. Then there are three recipes where metadata or category headers sit above the actual title, throwing off the extraction. And one case where the title spans multiple lines and gets partially captured.\n\nThe last two recipes have a different issue—they start with leftover content from the previous page, so the extractor grabs the wrong text thinking it's the title. All eleven of these are generated files, so the patterns are consistent artifacts of how the OCR and extraction pipeline handles these edge cases.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11815,"cache_read_input_tokens":10352,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":11815},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9478ca30-75ae-4ad8-8800-4ef68cfc301d","uuid":"0b6c969c-9c54-4940-b953-6868803ed5eb"}
